This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as Word Sense Induction (WSI) and language modeling. Additionally, the use of a recurrent language model (RNN-LM) is a common technique in NLP research. 

The paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses a neural language model and employs clustering techniques to induce senses. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with the task of WSI, which is a fundamental problem in AI research. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper uses a neural language model (RNN-LM) to improve the accuracy of WSI. 

Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the task of WSI, which is relevant to information retrieval tasks such as document classification and search.
